# Game builder template

## Architecture

- **Stack**: Vite, React, TypeScript, `react-router-dom`. Feature layout: `src/game/` (pure rules), `src/pages/`, `src/lib/`.
- **Entry**: `applyGamePresetsFromEnv()` in `src/main.tsx` runs before render; sets `data-game-type`, `data-deliverable`, `data-audience` on `document.documentElement`.

## Presets

- Game type, deliverable, audience, art direction: manifests in `src/lib/*Presets.ts`; see `PRESETS.md`.
- Env: `VITE_GAME_TYPE`, `VITE_GAME_DELIVERABLE`, `VITE_GAME_AUDIENCE`, `VITE_GAME_MULTIPLAYER`, `VITE_GAME_TITLE`.

## Artifacts

- Player rules: **only** root `RULES.md`. Sync to `public/RULES.md` when building digital-web.
- Designer docs: `GAME_SPEC.md`, `COMPONENTS.md`, `BALANCE.md`, `PLAYTEST.md`, `CHECKLIST.md`, `ASSUMPTIONS.md`.
- Print: **SVG only** under `assets/print/`; generated output in `assets/print/generated/` (gitignored).
- Card art: image generation allowed; prefer SVG composition for print.

## Quality

- TypeScript **strict**; `npm run typecheck` before calling digital deliverable done.
- v1 digital: **hot-seat** default; multiplayer network is experimental.

## Revamp skill

- Use `@game-build` (`.cursor/skills/game-build/SKILL.md`) for full workflow.
- One repo per game; `game-input/` is gitignored per-game drops.
